<p>I have been facing a rare issue only in IE and Edge. In my application, there is a input textbox. On typing a sentence or even a word, if I press enter in the middle of my word, it not only submits the form, but also breaks the word at that point. It looks like a new line getting appended, but that is not the case.</p>  <p>Following are the solutins I have tried, but with no result: 1) Restricting the text box to a single line box 2) Overriding the onkeypress function 3) CSS tweaks with white-space, word-wrap, word-break (<a href="http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/" rel="nofollow">http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/</a>)</p>  <p>Anyone has faced this issue before, and has any insights?</p>  <pre><code> HTML     &lt;input tabindex="5" type="search" id="searchTextbox" placeholder="search" ng-model="model.searchText" ng-change="populateSearchSuggestion()" key-trap="search" searchval="model.searchText" key-function="setSearchText()"&gt;   CSS .item-search-box {   display: block;   float: left;   position: relative;   width: 75%;   height: 70px;   border-left: solid 1px #f2f2f2;   padding: 12px;   padding-bottom: 0; }   @media screen and (min-width: 1650px) {     .item-search-box {       width: 80%; } }   .item-search-box i {     display: block;     font-size: 20px;     position: absolute;     top: 22px;     left: 20px;     opacity: 0.8; }   .item-search-box input[type="search"] {     display: block;     float: left;     width: calc(100% - 200px);     border: none;     height: 45px;     padding: 0 0 3px 40px;     font-size: 18px;     background: transparent;     white-space: nowrap;     overflow: hidden;     text-overflow: ellipsis;     border: solid 1px #e7e7e7;         /*border-radius: $bradius; */ }     .item-search-box input[type="search"]:-ms-input-placeholder {       color: #cccccc; }     .item-search-box input[type="search"]::-ms-clear {       color: #b3b3b3;       width: 30px;       cursor: pointer; }     .item-search-box input[type="search"]::-ms-clear:hover {       color: #333; }     .item-search-box input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button {       position: relative;       right: 20px; }     .item-search-box {         white-space: nowrap;         word-wrap: normal;         word-break: keep-all;     } </code></pre>